    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense for the economic side. but what about the social/cultural arguments? like, some people back then argued that segregation or keeping certain communities separate was actually better for \"cultural preservation\" or preventing social friction. can you expand on that logic? i really need to see how they framed the idea that separation was actually a \"positive\" or a \"necessity\" for social harmony to make my debate prep more realistic.",
